cs.LO, cs.FL, cs.DS, cs.PL, cs.CC 

The paper deals with automata models for data words and their expressive power in terms of existential monadic second order logic. This falls under the category of logic and computation (cs.LO). Additionally, the paper discusses the nonemptiness problem for weak data automata, which is a problem in formal languages and automata theory (cs.FL). The study of weak B\"uchi automata on data omega-strings also falls under formal languages and automata theory (cs.FL) as well as the study of complexity classes (cs.CC). Finally, the paper establishes complexity bounds for the nonemptiness problem using reductions, which is a technique used in computational complexity theory (cs.DS) and programming languages (cs.PL).
